reviewText: A decent western but not up to the level of  say "The Bounty Hunter"  and several other randolph scott westerns.

I paid 2.99$ for a 60 year old movie that kept stopping on me. This is not my new puter doing this. I am tired of paying this money for old movies that won't play through. I took me over 2 hour to watch a hour and forty minute movie.
I had difficulty in watching this movie. I had 26 days to watch this movie and it locked me out after 1.
another excellent randolp scott movie the color is good picture is sharp and clear it should be on blueray that would great.
A good western in Randolph Scott's tradition. If you enjoy westerns, you will enjoy this. If you like Randolph Scott westerns, you will like this one, too. They go together, hand and glove.
Good one; Randolph is one of my favorite cowboys.
